messages.text: Mary? I need you to come to Mount Peace Cemetery.
David, are you kidding me??!
It’s almost three a.m.
Why would I go to a cemetery that late at night??
Please? Do it for me?
Ugh, honestly, I don’t want to do anything for you right now.
I love you, but…
You left my apartment without even telling me.
Hey! I wrote you a note.
Yeah, and you put it in the kitchen!
Do you know how scared I was during those ten minutes it took me to find it?
Shit, I didn’t even think about that.
Sorry.
It’s okay. It’s just…this isn’t like you.
What’s really going on?
You said you were picking up Samson, but babe, you’re in a CEMETERY.
I am.
Samson woke up on a grave, Mary.
WHAT?!
I know, it was horrible.
He said his clothes were all torn and there was blood on his hands.
OMG!
I know, right? He’s pretty scared.
No, David. I’m not worried about Samson right now.
I’m worried about YOU.
You’re the one who’s tracking down your wild roommate.
And you followed him into a damn graveyard.
Mary, you know he isn’t actually wild.
He’s just going through a hard time.
David, has Samson even bothered to shave this month?
No—I don’t think he’s SHOWERED in a week.
That’s so gross.
There’s something wrong with him, David. Mark my words.
Look, I already said it—he’s going through a hard time.
He might look a little wild with the hair and everything right now…
But he was always a good friend to me.
Yeah, maybe before this year.
He gets really angry, David.
I’ve seen him literally SCREAM at you.
And when he gets like that, it’s like…it’s almost like he could hurt you.
What?
Admit it.
Have you ever thought that Samson might hurt you?
Sweetheart, let’s not get into this conversation right now.
I just want to go home.
Can you please get in a cab?
I AM in a cab.
I’m coming to help you because I think you might be in danger.
And I want you to be aware of your surroundings.
And know that you’re in danger too.
Mary, STOP.
I AM freaking out, okay? Is that what you want to hear?
I’m in this terrible, creepy graveyard at three in the morning.
And?
AND I’M TERRIFIED OF MY ROOMMATE.
He completely changed after his brother died.
What? I saw you typing…what were you going to say?
OMG, David, are you okay??!
Yeah, I’m right here.
It’s just—this might sound really stupid.
It’s okay, David. It’s me.
You don’t have to worry about feeling stupid in front of me.
Okay. It’s just—whenever Samson gets angry, he gets this look in his eyes.
It’s like something takes over inside his body.
And tonight, he completely blacked out.
He doesn’t remember anything he did.
He woke up with blood on his hands and all these scratches.
With the beard, and the hair, and the look in his eyes—
David, just say it. What are you trying to tell me?
I don’t know how to explain it.
Look—there’s a full moon tonight, Mary.
Samson doesn’t always get angry, and he doesn’t always black out—
But he did TONIGHT.
Maybe it has something to do with that full moon.
David, just say it.
You aren’t making ANY sense.
Ugh, fine. What if Samson is a werewolf?
David, be serious. There’s no such thing as werewolves.
This isn’t an episode of Teen Wolf.
Sweetheart, I AM serious.
There’s something wrong with Samson.
And he gets angry, it’s like he TRANSFORMS.
Well…he does have all that hair on his body.
I mean, let’s says he IS a werewolf.
What would we do any differently?
Well, we definitely can’t just leave him here.
When he isn’t a werewolf… he’s my best friend.
two minutes later
Holy shit! I just heard a howling noise!
Yeah, I heard it too.
Maybe you were right…
Wait, you’re here already??
Yeah. We just pulled up to the cemetery gates.
David, I’m scared. That noise definitely didn’t sound human.
I know. Are you still in the cab?
Yeah.
Good—DON’T get out.
I feel so exposed out here.
Like he could come up behind me at any moment.
OMG, David! Don’t say that.
You’re freaking me out.
It’s okay, I just found this big gravestone.
I crouched below it and put my back to it.
I’ll keep an eye on what’s in front of me.
Okay, thank God.
Yeah, and besides—the noise didn’t seem to be coming from close by.
Really? Because it sounds like it was right next to me…
What??
I don’t like that.
Look, Mary, just go home.
Forget about me. I’ll call an Uber or something.
No, David. I’m not leaving you out here in a graveyard with your werewolf roommate.
But you could get hurt!
And if you did, I’d never forgive myself for dragging you out here.
Please Mary? Please go home.
Too late for that.
What? Why?
He’s here.
There’s a werewolf standing outside my cab window.
